//Mediastinal vessels - Coronary anomaly

Given	I'm logged-in with valid credentials
And	I'm on Page 09 of Cardio MRI
When I select 'Finding' radio button
Then Finding dropdown menu is enabled

When I select 'Mediastinal vessels' from the dropdown menu
Then 'Add new finding' button is enabled
And 'Coronary anomaly' radio button is enabled
And 'Aorta' radio button is enabled
And 'Pulmonary arteries' radio button is enabled
And 'Pulmonary veins' radio button is enabled
And 'Vena cava' radio button is enabled


When I select 'Coronary anomaly' radio button
Then 'Origin' radio button is enabled
And 'Distal' radio button is enabled


// Origin radio button section
When I select 'Origin' radio button
Then 'High take off' radio button is enabled
And 'Missing LMA, separated ostia LAD & CX' radio button is enabled
And 'Singular coronary artery' radio button is enabled
And 'RCA from the left coronary sinus' radio button is enabled
And 'RCX / LAD from the right coronary sinus' radio button is enabled
And 'LMA from right coronary sinus' radio button is enabled

When I select 'RCA from the left coronary sinus' radio button
Then 'Prepulmonary' radio button is enabled
And 'Interarterial' radio button is enabled
And 'Retroaortic' radio button is enabled
And 'Septal' radio button is enabled

When I select 'RCX / LAD from the right coronary sinus' radio button
Then 'Prepulmonary' radio button is enabled in Progression RCX section
And 'Interarterial' radio button is enabled in Progression RCX section
And 'Retroaortic' radio button is enabled in Progression RCX section
And 'Septal' radio button is enabled in Progression RCX section
And 'Prepulmonary' radio button is enabled in Progression LAD  section
And 'Interarterial' radio button is enabled in Progression LAD  section
And 'Retroaortic' radio button is enabled in Progression LAD  section
And 'Septal' radio button is enabled in Progression LAD  section

When I select 'LMA from right coronary sinus' radio button
Then 'Prepulmonary' radio button is enabled
And 'Interarterial' radio button is enabled
And 'Retroaortic' radio button is enabled
And 'Septal' radio button is enabled


// Distal radio button section
When I select 'Distal' radio button
Then 'Myocardial bridge' radio button is enabled
And 'Ectasia/aneurysm' radio button is enabled
And 'RCA' checkbox is enabled
And 'LMA' checkbox is enabled
And 'LAD' checkbox is enabled
And 'RCX' checkbox is enabled
